  <div class="views-field views-field-field-htetrans">        <div class="field-content"><br>à¤¤à¤¤: thereafter, à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤­à¤¾à¤¤à¥ at dawn, à¤®à¤¹à¤°à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤­à¤¿: by maharshis, à¤à¥à¤¤à¤à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¾ having performed daily (sacrificial) acts, à¤µà¤¾à¤à¥à¤¯à¤à¥à¤: conversant in speech, à¤à¤¨à¤: Janaka, à¤ªà¥à¤°à¥à¤¹à¤¿à¤¤à¤®à¥ chief priest, à¤¶à¤¤à¤¾à¤¨à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¤®à¥ Satananda, à¤µà¤¾à¤à¥à¤¯à¤®à¥ words, à¤à¤µà¤¾à¤ said.<br></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-field-explanation">        <div class="field-content"><br>Thereafter at dawn after the maharshis had performed their daily (sacrificial) rites the eloquent Janaka said to the chief priest Satananda:<br></div>  </div>  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content">à¤­à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¤à¤¾ à¤®à¤® à¤®à¤¹à¤¾à¤¤à¥à¤à¤¾ à¤¯à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¨à¤¤à¤¿à¤§à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¿à¤:à¥¤<br><br>à¤à¥à¤¶à¤§à¥à¤µà¤ à¤à¤¤à¤¿ à¤à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¤: à¤ªà¥à¤°à¥à¤®à¤§à¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¸à¤à¥à¤à¥à¤­à¤¾à¤®à¥à¥¤à¥¤1.70.2à¥¤à¥¤<br><br>à¤µà¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤«à¤²à¤à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤¯à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¤¾à¤ à¤ªà¤¿à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤à¥à¤·à¥à¤®à¤¤à¥à¤ à¤¨à¤¦à¥à¤®à¥à¥¤<br><br>à¤¸à¤¾à¤à¥à¤à¤¾à¤¶à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ à¤ªà¥à¤£à¥à¤¯à¤¸à¤à¥à¤à¤¾à¤¶à¤¾à¤ à¤µà¤¿à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤®à¤¿à¤µ à¤ªà¥à¤·à¥à¤ªà¤à¤®à¥à¥¤à¥¤1.70.3à¥¤à¥¤<br><br></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-field-htetrans">        <div class="field-content"><br>à¤à¤¤à¤¿à¤§à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¿à¤: extremely righteous, à¤à¥à¤¶à¤§à¥à¤µà¤: à¤à¤¤à¤¿  named Kusadhwaja, à¤à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¤: renowned, à¤®à¤¹à¤¾à¤¤à¥à¤à¤¾: most brilliant, à¤®à¤® my, à¤¯à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¨à¥ younger, à¤­à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¤à¤¾ brother, à¤à¤à¥à¤·à¥à¤®à¤¤à¥à¤®à¥ named Ikshumati, à¤¨à¤¦à¥à¤®à¥ river, à¤ªà¤¿à¤¬à¤¨à¥ drinking, à¤µà¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤«à¤²à¤à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤¯à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¤¾à¤®à¥ darts planted in water as boundary, à¤¶à¥à¤­à¤¾à¤®à¥ auspicious, à¤ªà¥à¤£à¥à¤¯à¤¸à¤à¥à¤à¤¾à¤¶à¤¾à¤®à¥ sacred, à¤¸à¤¾à¤à¥à¤à¤¾à¤¶à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¥à¤®à¥ named Sankasya, à¤ªà¥à¤·à¥à¤ªà¤à¤®à¥ Pushpaka, à¤µà¤¿à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤®à¤¿à¤µ like chariot, à¤à¤§à¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¸à¤¤à¥ is residing.  <br></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-field-explanation">        <div class="field-content"><br>"The extremely righteous, renowned and most brilliant Kusadhwaja, my younger brother is (at present) ruling the sacred kingdom of Sankasya, which is like the aerial chariot Pushpaka, with darts planted in water as boundary on the bank of the auspicious, sacred river Ikshumati.  <br></div>  </div>  </div>
